File: A former Transnet employee appeared before the State Capture Inquiry on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - Former Transnet employee Gerhard van der Westhuizen has accused ex-CEO Brian Molefe of steamrolling decisions. Van der Westhuizen told the State Capture Inquiry that Molefe put Transnet at risk by allegedly favouring T-Systems for a network contract. LIVESTREAM: Transnet in the spotlight at Zondo Commission He suggested that the German company was not the best choice but says Molefe did not want to listen. "So, Chair, ultimately he was the decision-maker in this regard. I expressed my views to him and I still disagreed with it but like he said he had the delegation to make the decision, he was appointed in that role by the Department of Public Enterprises as my superior and I had to respect that”, said Van der Westhuizen